    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dark brown or black solid to semisolid material that is the organic, or hydrocarbon, portion of asphalt. It was used in ancient times as a sealant, for example in ancient Egypt. It is currently is used in hot-melt adhesives, coating, paints, sealants, roofing, and road coating.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
